        "observed_type": "caption",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Figure 11-4. High-side Switching with an NPN BJT Driving a PNP BJT",
        "bbox": [
          0.14312977282043335,
          0.23536706332223556,
          0.7175572582864368,
          0.2529761903063625
        ],
        "order": 8
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_book_en_搬书匠-3246-Electronics Cookbook-2017-英文版_page_193_7",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Low-side switching (Recipe 11.1) is the most common and simplest arrangement, and unless you have a good reason such as the need for one end of the load to be connected to ground, you should use low-side switching.",
        "bbox": [
          0.14122137182965058,
          0.2732558146517318,
          0.8606870267607253,
          0.3299418602085543
        ],
        "order": 9
      }
    ]
  },
